    <text>
        <body>
            <head>119. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rectQC2yY4UhXLeKu">Brzezinski</persName>) to President
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d119fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, President’s Correspondence with
                    Foreign Leaders File, Box 13, Libya: Secretary General Mu’ammar Qadhafi,
                    3/77–1/80. Secret. Sent for information. <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8"
                        >Carter</persName> wrote “Zbig, Push them on <gloss target="#t_UN_1">
                        <orgName corresp="recakWMbLwDF9eCZ8">UN</orgName>
                    </gloss> vote and public condemnation of SU. J” in the upper right-hand corner
                    of the memorandum.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1980-01-03"
                        >January 3, 1980</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Message from <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec2dRdHCd9ors2ln">Ali al-Houderi</persName> of the <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> People’s Bureau returned urgently
                from a visit to Tripoli yesterday to deliver a message from Col. <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>. He called me at noon today and
                read the following message from “Brother <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU"
                    >Qadhafi</persName>” to be passed to you:</p>
            <p>“1. <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> condemns the <placeName
                    corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3">Soviet</placeName> aggression in <placeName
                    corresp="recEtq3Tgt96SEVf9">Afghanistan</placeName>
                <note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d119fn2">
                    <placeName corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3">Soviet</placeName> troops <rs
                        type="event" corresp="recdLwDoSqvPQ5j12">invaded Afghanistan</rs> December
                    24–25, 1979.</note> and is very disturbed by it.</p>
            <p>“2. While <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> tries to maintain
                ties with the Soviets, because they are our major supplier of arms which we need to
                defend ourselves, this is because the United States denies us the arms which we need
                to defend ourselves.</p>
            <p>“3. You (the United States) are the superpower. You should do something to stop this
                aggression, which we see not only as a threat to <placeName
                    corresp="recEtq3Tgt96SEVf9">Afghanistan</placeName> but to the entire <placeName
                    corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName>. We will support any action
                which the United States is able to do, or is capable of thinking of, to stop this
                    <placeName corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3">Soviet</placeName> imperialism. We are
                willing to work closely with you on this.”</p>
            <p>I told <persName corresp="rec2dRdHCd9ors2ln">Houderi</persName> that if he had any
                concrete suggestions, we would be interested in hearing them. He said he had none at
                this time. I suggested that he might ask.</p>
            <p>I said we would also be interested in knowing whether <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> is willing to act in the <orgName
                    corresp="recakWMbLwDF9eCZ8">United Nations</orgName> to condemn the <placeName
                    corresp="rec7g4kEoiXWBjoX3">Soviet</placeName> actions. We believe that if <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recAgu4u4GprMJCKN">Third World</rs> nations are willing to
                take this step, it would be more important than just the U.S. and its <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recydYSQ1GmGAh8yu">allies</rs>. He said he
                would transmit this and wait for a reply.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
